1
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,026
Okay, I checked.

2
00:00:04,234 --> 00:00:07,897
We have Earl Grey, English Breakfast,
Cinnamon Stick...

3
00:00:08,205 --> 00:00:11,868
...Chamomile, Mint Medley,
Blackberry and...

4
00:00:12,142 --> 00:00:14,804
Wait, there's one more.
Lemon Soother!

5
00:00:16,714 --> 00:00:20,013
You're not the guy that asked
for tea, are you?

6
00:00:22,153 --> 00:00:24,246
The One Where The Monkey Gets Away

7
00:01:12,002 --> 00:01:14,562
Mail call!
Rachel Greene, bunk seven.

8
00:01:14,772 --> 00:01:16,399
Thank you.

9
00:01:17,608 --> 00:01:20,873
Oh, cool!
A free sample of coffee.

10
00:01:21,078 --> 00:01:24,980
Oh, good. Because where else
would we get any?

11
00:01:25,749 --> 00:01:27,512
Oh, right.

12
00:01:29,086 --> 00:01:31,520
-Oh, great.
-What is it?

13
00:01:31,722 --> 00:01:33,553
Country club newsletter.

14
00:01:33,791 --> 00:01:38,592
My mother sends me the engagement
notices for inspiration.

15
00:01:39,530 --> 00:01:43,296
Oh, my God! It's Barry and Mindy!

16
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:45,398
Barry, who you almost...

17
00:01:45,602 --> 00:01:47,194
And Mindy, your maid of...

18
00:01:47,438 --> 00:01:49,963
Let me see. That's Mindy?

19
00:01:50,207 --> 00:01:51,401
She is pretty!

20
00:01:53,811 --> 00:01:54,971
Lucky...

21
00:01:56,547 --> 00:02:00,142
...to have had a friend like you.

22
00:02:00,951 --> 00:02:03,419
Now it's quiet time.

23
00:02:09,026 --> 00:02:11,893
Marcel, bring me the rice. Come on.

24
00:02:12,129 --> 00:02:13,858
Good boy. Give me the rice.

25
00:02:14,131 --> 00:02:15,792
Thank you. Good boy.

26
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:21,332
He's mastered the difference between
"bring me the" and "pee in the."

27
00:02:23,841 --> 00:02:26,674
"Bring me the" and...
Rach?

28
00:02:28,846 --> 00:02:30,404
Oh, I'm sorry.

29
00:02:31,381 --> 00:02:33,042
This is so stupid!

30
00:02:33,317 --> 00:02:35,444
I mean, I gave Barry up, right?

31
00:02:35,652 --> 00:02:37,711
I should be happy for them.

32
00:02:37,921 --> 00:02:39,616
I am. I'm happy for them.

33
00:02:40,257 --> 00:02:42,657
-Really?
-No.

34
00:02:43,327 --> 00:02:46,854
I guess it would be different
if I were with somebody.

35
00:02:47,064 --> 00:02:48,429
Whoa, what...

36
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:53,898
What happened to "Forget
relationships! I'm done with men!"

37
00:02:54,104 --> 00:02:56,937
The whole penis embargo?

38
00:03:01,345 --> 00:03:02,437
I don't know.

39
00:03:02,679 --> 00:03:06,877
It's not about no guys.
It's about the right guy.

40
00:03:07,151 --> 00:03:11,315
With Barry it was safe and easy,
but there was no heat.

41
00:03:11,555 --> 00:03:14,922
With Paolo, all there was, was heat.

42
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:19,789
-It was this raw, animal, sexual...
-Right. I got it.

43
00:03:20,631 --> 00:03:21,859
I was there.

44
00:03:22,833 --> 00:03:24,994
Do you think you can have both?

45
00:03:25,202 --> 00:03:29,969
Someone who's your best friend
but also can make your toes curl.

46
00:03:30,174 --> 00:03:32,267
Yes.

47
00:03:32,476 --> 00:03:35,001
Yes, I do. I really do.

48
00:03:35,579 --> 00:03:37,547
In fact, it's funny.

49
00:03:37,748 --> 00:03:40,717
Often, someone
you wouldn't think could...

50
00:03:41,351 --> 00:03:43,182
...curl your toes...

51
00:03:43,387 --> 00:03:45,753
...might just be the one who...

52
00:03:47,224 --> 00:03:48,589
...gets interrupted.

53
00:03:48,859 --> 00:03:50,451
How was the movie?

54
00:03:50,661 --> 00:03:52,356
-Wonderful!
-So good!

55
00:03:52,563 --> 00:03:55,498
-Suck fest.
-Total chick flick.

56
00:03:57,601 --> 00:04:02,163
I'm sorry it wasn't one of those
movies with guns and bombs...

57
00:04:02,372 --> 00:04:04,602
...and buses going really fast!

58
00:04:06,944 --> 00:04:09,538
I don't need violence
in a movie...

59
00:04:09,813 --> 00:04:12,475
...as long as
there's a little nudity.

60
00:04:12,783 --> 00:04:16,241
-There was nudity.
-I meant female nudity.

61
00:04:16,453 --> 00:04:19,820
I don't need to see
Lou Grant frolicking.

62
00:04:20,023 --> 00:04:21,957
Hugh! Hugh Grant!

63
00:04:24,027 --> 00:04:26,018
All right, I've got to go.

64
00:04:26,230 --> 00:04:27,663
Come on, Marcel.

65
00:04:27,864 --> 00:04:31,664
We're gonna go take a bath.
Yes, we are, aren't we?

66
00:04:32,135 --> 00:04:35,161
They're still just friends, right?

67
00:04:38,408 --> 00:04:40,535
And I will see you tomorrow.

68
00:04:40,811 --> 00:04:43,803
You're gonna spend
tomorrow at Aunt Rachel's.

69
00:04:44,014 --> 00:04:46,847
Does Aunt Monica get a say in this?

70
00:04:47,517 --> 00:04:49,917
Please, Aunt Monica, please?

71
00:04:50,153 --> 00:04:53,418
Unclench. You're not even
gonna be here.

72
00:04:58,929 --> 00:05:04,765
-I can't believe we're discussing this.
-I agree. I'm, like, in disbelief.

73
00:05:05,335 --> 00:05:08,793
If it was gonna happen,
wouldn't it have happened already?

74
00:05:09,172 --> 00:05:13,632
She said she wants a relationship
with someone exactly like me.

75
00:05:13,877 --> 00:05:15,139
She said that?

76
00:05:15,379 --> 00:05:18,678
I added the "exactly like me" part.

77
00:05:19,049 --> 00:05:23,543
But she's looking for someone.
And someone will be there tonight.

78
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,051
"Tonight" tonight?

79
00:05:25,355 --> 00:05:28,119
It's perfect.
It'll just be the two of us.

80
00:05:28,325 --> 00:05:31,954
She spent all day
taking care of my monkey.

81
00:05:33,897 --> 00:05:38,027
I can't remember the last time
a girl took care of my monkey.

82
00:05:42,005 --> 00:05:45,998
Anyway, I figured after work,
I'd pick up some wine...

83
00:05:46,209 --> 00:05:49,906
...go over there and try to woo her.

84
00:05:51,448 --> 00:05:53,006
Know what you should do?

85
00:05:53,216 --> 00:05:57,516
Take her back to the 1890s
when that phrase was last used.

86
00:06:01,224 --> 00:06:05,354
<i>If you keep this up, you'll be
finished by the weekend.</i>

87
00:06:05,796 --> 00:06:08,856
The one in the feathered boa
is Dr. Francis.

88
00:06:09,099 --> 00:06:11,431
Now, she used to be a man.

89
00:06:12,169 --> 00:06:13,500
Look, there's Raven.

90
00:06:13,704 --> 00:06:17,105
We hate her. We're glad she's dying.

91
00:06:17,441 --> 00:06:19,773
And then...
What? Marcel!

92
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:24,146
Are you playing with Monica's shoes?
You're not supposed to...

93
00:06:26,450 --> 00:06:29,886
Marcel, did you poo in the shoe?

94
00:06:30,087 --> 00:06:32,851
Oh, Marcel! Bad monkey!

95
00:06:33,323 --> 00:06:36,019
Oh, God!

96
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:42,130
Sorry, Barry.

97
00:06:42,632 --> 00:06:44,725
A little engagement gift.

98
00:06:44,968 --> 00:06:47,903
I'm sure you didn't
register for that.

99
00:06:55,545 --> 00:06:57,809
Who died? Who died?

100
00:06:58,014 --> 00:07:00,744
Roll him over!
Come on, roll him over!

101
00:07:01,718 --> 00:07:05,984
Well, we know it wasn't Dexter,
right, Marcel? Because...

102
00:07:06,189 --> 00:07:07,178
Marcel?

103
00:07:11,261 --> 00:07:13,661
-How could you lose him?
-I don't know!

104
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:17,266
We were watching TV,
he pooped in Monica's shoe...

105
00:07:17,467 --> 00:07:20,402
Wait. He pooped in my shoe?
Which one?

106
00:07:20,604 --> 00:07:23,505
I don't know. The left one!

107
00:07:23,707 --> 00:07:24,765
Which ones?

108
00:07:24,975 --> 00:07:29,309
Those little clunky Amish things
you think go with everything.

109
00:07:33,016 --> 00:07:36,179
Why is the air in here so negative?

110
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,849
Rachel lost Marcel.

111
00:07:39,122 --> 00:07:40,111
Oh, no! How?

112
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:42,349
-He pooped in my shoe.
-Which one?

113
00:07:42,592 --> 00:07:44,856
The cute black ones I always wear.

114
00:07:45,162 --> 00:07:47,221
No, which one?

115
00:07:47,431 --> 00:07:49,865
The right or left?

116
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:52,428
Because the left one is lucky.

117
00:07:52,669 --> 00:07:54,432
Come on!
What am I gonna do?

118
00:07:54,604 --> 00:07:58,199
All right. You're a monkey.
You're loose in the city.

119
00:07:58,475 --> 00:08:00,409
Where do you go?

120
00:08:00,777 --> 00:08:04,543
It's his first time out,
so he'll do touristy things.

121
00:08:07,617 --> 00:08:11,417
I'll go to <i>Cats</i>.
You go to the Russian Tea Room.

122
00:08:11,988 --> 00:08:14,650
Oh, my God!
Come on, you guys!

123
00:08:14,891 --> 00:08:17,382
He'll be home any minute.
He's gonna kill me!

124
00:08:17,594 --> 00:08:21,826
Search the building. Take the first
floor. We'll take the rest.

125
00:08:22,065 --> 00:08:23,430
What am I gonna do?

126
00:08:23,667 --> 00:08:26,135
You stay here
and wait by the phone.

127
00:08:26,336 --> 00:08:29,931
Spray Lysol in my shoe
and wait for Ross to kill you.

128
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:32,506
Does anybody want to trade?

129
00:08:39,816 --> 00:08:41,249
What do you want?

130
00:08:41,451 --> 00:08:44,818
Mr. Heckles, have you seen a monkey?

131
00:08:45,021 --> 00:08:48,422
I left a Belgian waffle out here.
Did you take it?

132
00:08:49,025 --> 00:08:52,961
-Why'd you leave it in the hall?
-I wasn't ready for it.

133
00:08:53,463 --> 00:08:55,454
Have you seen a monkey?

134
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:58,463
I saw Regis Philbin once.

135
00:08:59,469 --> 00:09:01,266
Thank you, Mr. Heckles.

136
00:09:02,372 --> 00:09:04,101
You owe me a waffle.

137
00:09:05,876 --> 00:09:09,403
He's a black capuchin monkey
with a white face...

138
00:09:09,646 --> 00:09:14,674
...with Russian dressing
and pickles on the side.

139
00:09:14,918 --> 00:09:16,044
Thanks.

140
00:09:17,821 --> 00:09:19,220
How did it go today?

141
00:09:19,422 --> 00:09:22,323
Oh, great!
It went great. Really great.

142
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:23,890
Is that wine?

143
00:09:24,628 --> 00:09:26,152
You want some?

144
00:09:26,363 --> 00:09:28,092
Oh, I would love some.

145
00:09:28,331 --> 00:09:30,663
But let's not drink it here.

146
00:09:30,901 --> 00:09:34,598
I'm feeling crazy.
You wanna go to Newark?

147
00:09:38,542 --> 00:09:43,912
Okay, but before we head off to
the murder capital of the Northeast...

148
00:09:44,281 --> 00:09:47,409
...I kind of wanted
to run something by you.

149
00:09:47,684 --> 00:09:50,244
You know how we
were talking before...

150
00:09:50,453 --> 00:09:53,286
...about relationships, and stuff.

151
00:09:53,490 --> 00:09:57,893
-Oh, God, Ross, I cannot do this!
-Okay, quick and painful.

152
00:10:06,403 --> 00:10:07,529
Oh, God!

153
00:10:07,904 --> 00:10:10,930
Okay, all right.
All right, okay.

154
00:10:11,141 --> 00:10:13,166
Please don't hate me.

155
00:10:13,376 --> 00:10:14,365
What?

156
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:19,111
You know Marcel?

157
00:10:22,619 --> 00:10:26,111
I kind of lost him.

158
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:43,667
I can't believe this.

159
00:10:43,974 --> 00:10:47,068
All I asked you to do was
keep him in here!

160
00:10:47,277 --> 00:10:48,437
I know. I'm sorry.

161
00:10:48,645 --> 00:10:50,545
It's partially my fault.

162
00:10:50,714 --> 00:10:53,512
I shouldn't have had you
start with a monkey.

163
00:10:53,683 --> 00:10:56,675
You should have started
with a pencil.

164
00:10:56,987 --> 00:11:01,720
I'm doing everything I can.
Everyone's looking for him and I got...

165
00:11:04,094 --> 00:11:05,857
-Who is it?
-<i>Animal Control.</i>

166
00:11:06,129 --> 00:11:11,123
-I've even got Animal Control.
-You called Animal Control?

167
00:11:13,003 --> 00:11:15,801
Why? Do you not like them?

168
00:11:18,274 --> 00:11:22,472
Marcel is an illegal exotic animal.

169
00:11:25,582 --> 00:11:30,679
I'm not allowed to have him. If they
find him, they'll take him away.

170
00:11:30,887 --> 00:11:34,186
Well, now, see,
you never ever told us that.

171
00:11:34,991 --> 00:11:39,121
Because I never expected you
to invite them to the apartment!

172
00:11:44,434 --> 00:11:45,833
Thanks for coming.

173
00:11:46,036 --> 00:11:48,197
Somebody called about a monkey?

174
00:11:48,405 --> 00:11:51,897
You know, that was
a complete misunderstanding.

175
00:11:52,108 --> 00:11:54,736
We thought we had a monkey,
but we didn't.

176
00:11:54,911 --> 00:11:56,845
-Turned out it was a hat.
-Cat!

177
00:11:59,082 --> 00:12:01,676
We checked, no one's seen Marcel.

178
00:12:01,885 --> 00:12:06,219
-My uncle Marcel.
-Is that who the monkey's named after?

179
00:12:07,123 --> 00:12:10,149
Possession of an illegal exotic
is punishable...

180
00:12:10,326 --> 00:12:13,853
...by two years in prison
and confiscation of the animal.

181
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:15,019
Oh, my God!

182
00:12:15,832 --> 00:12:19,165
You'd put that poor
little creature in jail?

183
00:12:23,773 --> 00:12:28,972
Remember how we talked about saying
things quietly to yourself first?

184
00:12:29,179 --> 00:12:32,706
Yes, but there isn't always time.

185
00:12:35,085 --> 00:12:39,852
I'm sure there's some friendly way
to reconcile this. Have a seat.

186
00:12:40,056 --> 00:12:42,524
We haven't met. I'm Monica Geller.

187
00:12:42,859 --> 00:12:45,419
Oh, my God, you are!

188
00:12:45,695 --> 00:12:47,322
And you're Rachel Greene!

189
00:12:49,032 --> 00:12:51,660
Luisa Gianetti! Lincoln High?

190
00:12:51,901 --> 00:12:55,234
I sat behind you guys in homeroom.

191
00:12:55,939 --> 00:12:59,170
Luisa! Oh, my God!

192
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:01,366
Monica! It's Luisa!

193
00:13:04,013 --> 00:13:05,446
I went there too!

194
00:13:05,648 --> 00:13:07,639
Luisa! From homeroom!

195
00:13:09,753 --> 00:13:12,517
You have no idea who I am, do you?

196
00:13:12,722 --> 00:13:14,314
-No.
-Not at all.

197
00:13:14,624 --> 00:13:19,254
Well, maybe that's because
you spent four years ignoring me.

198
00:13:19,462 --> 00:13:23,228
Would it have been hard to say,
"Morning, Luisa"...

199
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:25,799
...or "Nice overalls"?

200
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:31,932
Oh, I'm so sorry!

201
00:13:32,142 --> 00:13:36,476
It's not so much you. You were fat.
You had your own problems.

202
00:13:38,448 --> 00:13:40,643
But you. What a bitch!

203
00:13:42,519 --> 00:13:43,781
What?

204
00:13:43,987 --> 00:13:46,421
You know what? Be that as it may...

205
00:13:46,623 --> 00:13:50,719
...could you help us with the
monkey thing, for old times' sake?

206
00:13:50,927 --> 00:13:52,895
Go, Bobcats!

207
00:13:53,496 --> 00:13:56,431
I could. But I won't.

208
00:13:56,633 --> 00:13:59,898
If I find that monkey, he's mine.

209
00:14:04,974 --> 00:14:06,908
Sorry.

210
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,304
Marcel?

211
00:14:11,981 --> 00:14:13,039
Marcel?

212
00:14:21,591 --> 00:14:23,422
Hi, can I help you?

213
00:14:27,597 --> 00:14:31,761
We're having an emergency,
and we were looking for something.

214
00:14:32,969 --> 00:14:35,631
-A monkey.
-Yes, have you seen any?

215
00:14:35,839 --> 00:14:38,273
No, I haven't seen a monkey.

216
00:14:38,474 --> 00:14:40,442
Can you fix radiators?

217
00:14:40,643 --> 00:14:44,044
Sure! Did you try turning the knob
back the other way?

218
00:14:44,347 --> 00:14:47,248
-Of course!
-Oh. Then, no.

219
00:14:51,454 --> 00:14:55,390
-Taste this. Is there too much rum?
-Just a second.

220
00:14:55,592 --> 00:14:58,152
-Hope you find your monkey.
-No, wait!

221
00:14:59,629 --> 00:15:02,029
We may not know about radiators...

222
00:15:02,298 --> 00:15:07,235
...but we do have expertise
in the heating and cooling milieu.

223
00:15:10,773 --> 00:15:13,173
Aren't we in the middle of something?

224
00:15:13,343 --> 00:15:17,211
But these women are very hot,
and they need our help.

225
00:15:17,947 --> 00:15:20,211
And they're very hot!

226
00:15:22,452 --> 00:15:23,919
We can't, all right?

227
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,585
We're sorry.

228
00:15:25,822 --> 00:15:29,724
You don't know how sorry.
We promised to find this monkey.

229
00:15:29,926 --> 00:15:33,054
He's this high
and answers to the name Marcel.

230
00:15:33,263 --> 00:15:37,597
So if we could get pictures of you,
it'd help us out.

231
00:15:45,642 --> 00:15:49,373
From now on, you don't get
to talk to other people.

232
00:15:57,820 --> 00:15:58,946
-Oh, my God!
-What?

233
00:15:59,155 --> 00:16:02,090
Something brushed up
against my right leg.

234
00:16:03,059 --> 00:16:06,119
Oh, it's okay.
It was just my left leg.

235
00:16:07,697 --> 00:16:08,686
Look, Phoebe!

236
00:16:09,432 --> 00:16:11,491
Oh, Marcel! Come here!

237
00:16:11,734 --> 00:16:13,258
Step aside, ladies.

238
00:16:14,938 --> 00:16:18,032
-What are you gonna do?
-Just a tranquilizer.

239
00:16:33,957 --> 00:16:35,788
Run, Marcel, run!

240
00:16:36,125 --> 00:16:37,114
Damn!

241
00:16:37,393 --> 00:16:40,692
-Are you okay?
-I think so.

242
00:16:49,138 --> 00:16:50,127
Oh, gosh!

243
00:17:01,584 --> 00:17:05,418
We've been all over the neighborhood!
He's just gone!

244
00:17:05,621 --> 00:17:08,749
-You don't know that.
-It's cold, it's dark.

245
00:17:08,958 --> 00:17:11,222
He doesn't know the Village!

246
00:17:11,427 --> 00:17:16,364
And now I have a broken foot.
I have no monkey and a broken foot!

247
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:17,861
Thank you very much!

248
00:17:18,067 --> 00:17:20,865
I've said I'm sorry a million times.

249
00:17:21,170 --> 00:17:22,797
What do you want me to do?

250
00:17:23,139 --> 00:17:26,973
You want me to break my foot too?
I'll break it right now.

251
00:17:27,176 --> 00:17:30,634
Oh, my God!
